## Role Assignments

### Owner Assignment

The following users will be granted the `{{ data_product_name | upper }}_ADMIN` role:

{%- for user in owner_users %}
- `{{ user | upper }}`
{%- endfor %}

These users will have full administrative control over:
- All databases and schemas in this data product
- Grant management for all data product roles
- Warehouse operations and monitoring

### Managing Reader and Writer Access

Reader and writer access should be managed separately through your organization's access management process.

#### Example Commands for Future Access Grants

**Grant reader access to a user:**
```sql
USE ROLE SECURITYADMIN;
GRANT ROLE {{ data_product_name | upper }}_READ TO USER <username>;
```

**Grant reader access to a group/parent role:**
```sql
USE ROLE SECURITYADMIN;
GRANT ROLE {{ data_product_name | upper }}_READ TO ROLE <team_role>;
```

{%- if role_structure == 'Full (Admin + Create + Write + Read)' %}

**Grant writer access to a user or service account:**
```sql
USE ROLE SECURITYADMIN;
GRANT ROLE {{ data_product_name | upper }}_WRITE TO USER <username>;
```

{%- endif %}

{%- if role_structure == 'Standard (Admin + Create + Read)' or role_structure == 'Full (Admin + Create + Write + Read)' %}

**Grant admin access for delegated management:**
```sql
USE ROLE SECURITYADMIN;
GRANT ROLE {{ data_product_name | upper }}_ADMIN TO USER <username>;
```

{%- endif %}

**Revoke access:**
```sql
USE ROLE SECURITYADMIN;
REVOKE ROLE {{ data_product_name | upper }}_READ FROM USER <username>;
```

### Best Practice: SCIM Integration

For ongoing access management, consider integrating with your Identity Provider:
- Map IdP groups to Snowflake roles
- Automate onboarding/offboarding
- Maintain audit trail in your IdP

See [SCIM Integration](https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/scim) for setup instructions.